Jan 29 (Reuters) - Airtel Africa PLC AAF.L:: *AIRTEL AFRICA SAYS 9-MONTH REPORTED REVENUE INCREASED BY 13.8% TO $2,870M WITH Q3'21 REPORTED REVENUE GROWTH OF 19.5% *9M UNDERLYING EBITDA ROSE 16 PERCENT TO 1.297 BILLION USD *9M BASIC EARNINGS PER SHARE FELL 36.5 PERCENT TO 0.055 USD *AIRTEL AFRICA-WHILE COVID-19 PANDEMIC HAS HAD LITTLE IMPACT ON OUR MOST RECENT QUARTER, REMAIN VIGILANT ABOUT RECENT NEWS FLOW AROUND NEW STRAINS OF VIRUS


((Reuters Investor Briefs; email: reutersinvestor.briefs@thomsonreuters.com)) Source Date/Time = 29-JAN-202107:15:01 GMT
